flex-diretion:row
X- axis is main axis and can be set using justify content
Y- axis is cross axis and can be set using align items

flex-diretion:column
Y axis is main axis and can be set using justify content
X- axis is cross axis and can be set using align items


PARENT :ROOM
CHILD:BOX
if parent has display flex in its style then children can be ordered using order tag
eg:class="box box1"
eg:class="box box2"
<style>
    .box1{
        order:3
    }
    .box2{
        order:2
    }
    .box3{
        order:1
    }
</style>
also increse the size of children using flex-grow
.box1{
    order: 3;
    flex-grow: 1;
}
.box2{
    order: 1;
    flex-grow: 1;

}

similar properties like
flex-shrink:1;
flex-basis:200px;//increase or decrease width
short hand flex: 0 0 200px;
"grow,shrink.basis:
